{
  "texts": [
    "With the exception of the SUS measurement, there are no reference or standard values for respondent behavior from other surveys.",
    "Therefore, the mean of the five-point Likert scale shown, i.e., 3, was taken as the baseline.",
    "For the SUS, the mean of 68 out of a maximum of 100 points was used based on existing surveys (Brooke, 2013; Sauro, 2011).",
    "Therefore, the values of 3 and 68 were used as the null hypothesis for the two-sided LRT.",
    "The results are presented in Table 4."
  ]
}